Water CS Eugene Wamalwa (pictured) has urged Luhyas and Luos to vote for Jubilee so they can benefit from extension of the SGR.Speaking yesterday in Kitale, Wamalwa said he has lobbied for the standard gauge railway to be extended from Nairobi-Kisumu-Busia in phase one and Nairobi-Nakuru-Eldoret-Kitale in phase two.&ldquo;This will only happen if you the people of Western vote in Jubilee government for a second term,&rdquo; he said.The government initially planned for SGR phase one from Mombasa to Nairobi and phase two from Nairobi to Malaba via Naivasha and Kisumu. Malaba is in Western and Kisumu in Nyanza.The CS also criticised NASA for &ldquo;politicising security issues&rdquo;, such as calling for the withdrawal of the KDF from Somalia.The soldiers were deployed to the country to keep Kenya safe from frequent al Shabaab attacks.